  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed across inlet boundary conditions and blood viscosity parameters; a screening sensitivity study was conducted verbally in the UQ report to identify potentially influential inputs, confirming that flow rate and rotational speed dominate hemolysis index variance. Structured sensitivity analysis results are incorporated into the UQ narrative.",
