  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels at MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per the MRL 2 assessment plan. Uncertainty quantification demonstrates that the 95th-percentile hemolysis index prediction remains below the RH < 1 acceptance criterion with adequate margin (RH_95 = 0.87). The UQ report documents a screening sensitivity study identifying flow rate and rotational speed as dominant contributors to output variance, supporting confidence that the model input space is adequately characterized. Validation activities used the identical pump geometry and operating conditions as the COU, and output comparison metrics satisfy the ±15% acceptance band. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory decision for this Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2.",
